<HEADLINE>
<P>
DR. PAUL SAFFO; PROMOTED BOTANIC GARDENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dr. Paul Saffo, 88, South Bay surgeon who promoted botanic gardens. A native 
of Bridgeport, Conn., Saffo was educated at Catholic University, Yale Medical 
School and Charles University in Prague, Czechoslovakia.After practicing in San 
Francisco, he settled in Los Angeles in 1941. Saffo helped establish Daniel 
Freeman Memorial Hospital and Centinela Hospital and was chief of staff and a 
trustee of the Robert F. Kennedy Medical Center in Hawthorne. A charter member 
of the South Coast Botanic Garden, Saffo served as its president from 1972 to 
1975. He also served on the board of governors of the Los Angeles County 
Arboreta and Botanic Gardens Commission, which oversees the county's three 
gardens -- South Bay, the Arboretum in Arcadia and Descanso Gardens in La 
Canada Flintridge. Saffo earned the Service to Mankind award from the Del Amo 
Sertoma Club in 1975. On Feb. 19 in Rolling Hills of lung cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
