<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: INGLEWOOD; COMEDIAN 
GARRETT MORRIS LISTED IN STABLE CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Comedian Garrett Morris was listed in serious but stable condition Friday at 
Daniel Freeman Memorial Hospital in Inglewood, where he had undergone surgery 
for gunshot wounds. 
</P>
<P>
 A bullet remained lodged near his spinal cord and will probably be surgically 
removed soon, although Morris is not paralyzed, Dr. Randy Hawkins told 
reporters. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's fortunate he did not have more severe injuries," said Hawkins, who 
described the actor as awake and alert. 
</P>
<P>
 The bullet pierced Morris' lower left arm and continued into his abdomen, 
damaging his small and large intestine, aorta and stomach before lodging in the 
spinal canal, Hawkins said. He characterized the arm wound as probably minor 
and the abdominal injuries as serious. 
</P>
<P>
 Morris' wife, Freda, briefly addressed reporters at the hospital news 
conference to thank her husband's supporters for their prayers. 
</P>
<P>
 "My husband is the most fortunate person," Morris said. "This is an 
unfortunate thing that can happen anywhere. I'm just sorry that it happened at 
all." 
</P>
