</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A memorial service has been scheduled for Monday for Christy Lynne Hamilton, 
the rookie Los Angeles Police Department officer who was killed Tuesday while 
responding to a domestic disturbance call. 
</P>
<P>
 Hamilton, 45, who graduated from the Police Academy on Feb. 18, was shot in 
Northridge by a 17-year-old who had killed his father and then took his own 
life.She was the LAPD's second female officer to die in the line of duty. 
</P>
<P>
 A viewing is planned from 4 to 9 p.m. Sunday at Forest Lawn's Hollywood Hills 
mortuary, 6300 Forest Lawn Drive, Los Angeles. The memorial service will be 
held Monday at 10:30 a.m. at Grace Community Church of the Valley, 13248 Roscoe 
Blvd., Sun Valley. Burial will follow at Forest Lawn Memorial-Park, Hollywood 
Hills. 
</P>
<P>
