<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LONG BEACH; $6.7 
MILLION ALLOCATED TO RETROFIT FREEWAY STRUCTURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Transportation Commission allocated $6.7 million this week to 
seismically retrofit 13 freeway structures in Long Beach, including parts of 
the San Diego Freeway-Long Beach Freeway interchange. The work will begin in 
July. 
