FREIGHT TRAIN KILLS TWICE IN SAME DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men at separate railroad crossings were killed by the same freight train 
on the same day, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Southern Pacific train first collided with a pickup Thursday morning at a 
crossing in Pine Bluff, killing James Edward Dallari, 43. After a 90-minute 
delay, the train took off with a new engineer at the controls. Less than five 
hours later and 50 miles down the tracks, the train struck a car at another 
crossing, killing Roderick Miguel Daniels, 21. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was not a good day for that train," said Mike Furtney, a Southern Pacific 
spokesman. "The weather was clear in both cases. You'd think somebody could see 
a train coming." 
</P>
