<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARGARET LANE; BIOGRAPHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Margaret Lane, 86, biographer of authors Beatrix Potter, Samuel Johnson and 
the Bronte sisters.After studying at Oxford University, she became one of the 
first women reporters on London's Fleet Street newspaper row in 1928. She wrote 
for the Daily Express, the Daily Mail and for the International News Service in 
New York before turning to books. In addition to biographies, she wrote four 
novels, including "Faith, Hope, No Charity" and "A Night at Sea," and several 
other books. She was president of London's Women's Press Club from 1958 to 1960 
and headed the Dickens Fellowship literary society, the Johnson Society, the 
Bronte Society and the Jane Austen Society. On Feb. 14 in Southampton, England. 
</P>
