<P>
2 DIE IN PLANE CRASH NEAR PALM SPRINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A small plane crashed into a mountainside near the Soboba Indian Reservation 
in Riverside County, killing two men, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The single-engine Cessna 150 went down Thursday at the 2,500-foot level of 
North Mountain, two miles north of the reservation, Federal Aviation 
Administration spokesman Fred O'Donnell said. 
</P>
<P>
 The area is about 15 miles west of Palm Springs. 
</P>
<P>
 Two men in their 30s were found dead at the scene. Authorities did not release 
their identities. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of the crash remained under investigation. 
</P>
