<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT TO REPLANT CHANNEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Moorpark branch of the Environmental Coalition and the city of Moorpark 
are looking for volunteers to help restore a stretch of the Arroyo Simi 
flood-control channel today and on March 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers are needed to help replant native vegetation in the channel between 
8:30 a.m. and 3 p.m. both days, coalition officials said in a prepared release. 
</P>
<P>
 On Feb. 19, 40 people helped plant more than 550 cuttings, and 10 of the 
volunteers won commemorative T-shirts while others were awarded prizes donated 
by local merchants. Coalition officials hope to plant more than 1,000 cuttings 
on each of the two remaining Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone who wants to participate should show up at the Teledyne Laars parking 
lot at 6000 Condor Drive in Moorpark. Those wishing to help are asked to bring 
hand clippers or pruning shears, and sharp pocket knives or heavy-duty loppers. 
Hand-held sledgehammers also are needed, and volunteers should wear long pants, 
work gloves, sunscreen, sunglasses and sturdy shoes that probably will get wet. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information or to volunteer, call Roseann Mikos at 529-4828 or Karen 
Rosenblum at 529-8904. JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
