<P>
COUNTYWIDE: NEW RESERVATION LINE TOLD FOR CAMPSITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U. S. Forest Service has a new phone number for reserving spaces at 
campgrounds, including two in Ventura County's backcountry, officials announced 
recently. 
</P>
<P>
 Individuals and groups can reserve camping sites by calling (800) 280-CAMP or 
(800) 879-4496 for the hearing-impaired.  
</P>
<P>
 The numbers replace reservation phone lines, officials said this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Operators will take reservation requests for Wheeler Gorge and McGill 
campgrounds in Los Padres National Forest north of Ojai, as well as at 154 
other camping sites across the country. 
</P>
<P>
 The reservation center will tell callers which campgrounds are available for 
advance reservations, officials said. KAY SAILLANT 
