<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARA BLOWS PAST LOYOLA, 98-58 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kevin Dunne scored a career-high 18 points Friday night as Santa Clara broke a 
three-game losing streak by routing Loyola Marymount, 98-58, in a West Coast 
Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 For the Broncos (13-12 and 6-7), it was the biggest margin of victory in a WCC 
game since they beat Portland, 103-59, in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the poorest performance of the season for Loyola, which committed 20 
turnovers in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Clara cruised to a 40-19 first-half lead as the Lions shot only 25% from 
the field. The Broncos stole the ball 11 times.  
</P>
<P>
 Loyola (6-19, 4-9) scored only one field goal over the final 10 minutes of the 
first half. 
</P>
<P>
 For the game, Santa Clara shot 51% and had a 50-31 rebounding edge. 
</P>
<P>
 Wyking Jones and Bill Mazurie had 14 points for Loyola. 
</P>
