<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOPEZ'S 27 LEAD WAVES TO NO. 2 SPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Damin Lopez made six-of-six three-pointers in the first half Friday night and 
led all scorers with 27 points to pace Pepperdine to an 88-65 victory over St. 
Mary's in Moraga, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
 Pepperdine improved to 15-10 overall and 7-6 in the West Coast Conference, 
moving into a second-place tie with San Francisco. St. Mary's fell to 12-13, 
4-9. 
</P>
<P>
 "I am pleased with our defensive intensity and the team is really sharing the 
ball," Pepperdine Coach Tom Asbury said. "And that opens up the offense." 
</P>
<P>
 The Waves started the game with a 20-9 run over the first 8:30, including four 
of Lopez's three-pointers. Accurate shooting and forward Dana Jones' 10 
first-half rebounds helped expand the Wave lead to 46-26 by the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the Gaels were only outscored 42-39 in the second half, they could 
get no closer than a 15-point deficit the rest of the way. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Mary's was outshot 59% to 32% from the floor. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones finished with 19 points and 16 rebounds. 
</P>
