<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANITA; SEMILLON FAVORED TO WIN THE SAN MARINO HANDICAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Semillon, called by Mike Mitchell the best horse he has ever trained, will be 
sent after his third consecutive U.S. victory in the $82,200 San Marino 
Handicap at Santa Anita today. 
</P>
<P>
 After making his first 13 starts in Europe, the 4-year-old Rousillon colt came 
to Mitchell late last year and has responded with two victories at Santa 
Anita.Eddie Delahoussaye will again ride Semillon, the 8-5 morning-line 
favorite in the 1 1/4-mile race. 
</P>
<P>
 Itsallgreektome, who came off a 14-month layoff to run second in an allowance 
race last month, is the 5-2 second choice. The 7-year-old gelding, now trained 
by Bob Hess, will be ridden by Kent Desormeaux and carry 120 pounds, four more 
than the favorite. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Antley was off his mounts again Friday after suffering a pulled groin 
muscle Wednesday. . . . Hollywood Wildcat won't run in the Santa Margarita 
Handicap on March 6 because of a cough. BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
