<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES AIDS CSUN JOURNALISM EFFORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Times Valley Edition has donated $23,000 to the quake-damaged 
journalism department at Cal State Northridge for replacement of the student 
publications' computer system, Valley Edition President Jeffrey S. Klein 
announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Klein said that while the publications are in temporary quarters, the new 
system can serve students who work on the Daily Sundial newspaper, reporters 
for public radio station KCSN-FM, and writers for CSUN's weekly cable news 
program, Valley View. 
</P>
<P>
 The equipment -- including a Macintosh Quadra 605 and 650 fileserver and an 
Apple 360 Laserprinter -- can then be integrated into a larger system when the 
publications move back into their permanent building, Klein said. 
</P>
<P>
 In a letter to CSUN President Blenda J. Wilson that accompanied the check, 
Klein noted that no institution experienced more financial loss than CSUN. 
</P>
<P>
 "We remain committed to the community, to CSUN (the alma mater of many Times 
employees) and especially to supporting quality journalism programs and 
university newspapers like the Daily Sundial," Klein wrote. 
</P>
</TEXT>
