<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN DART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TWO AT TWENTY-FIVE: The senior pastors of the east San Fernando Valley's 
biggest evangelical churches are marking 25 years in their respective posts. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rev. John MacArthur, 54, observed a quarter-century at the pulpit of Grace 
Community Church in Sun Valley this month.The Rev. W. A. Criswell of Dallas 
First Baptist Church was a guest preacher at the service honoring MacArthur. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rev. Jack Hayford, 59, on June 19 will celebrate his 25 years of pastoring 
at the First Foursquare Church of Van Nuys, familiarly known as the Church on 
the Way. 
</P>
<P>
 SPEAKER: Jerry Levin, the former CNN Beirut bureau chief who was taken hostage 
in Lebanon, will speak during the 10 a.m. service Sunday at Van Nuys First 
Presbyterian Church, 14701 Friar St. An adult forum with Levin will follow at 
11 a.m. For details, call (818) 786-6230. 
</P>
<P>
 MUSIC/COMEDY: A fund-raising concert of Jewish and American music and comedy 
at Valley Beth Shalom in Encino at 7 p.m. Sunday will feature Cantors Herschel 
and Judy Fox, pianist Elliot Finkel and comedian Dave Barry. For information, 
call (818) 788-6000. 
</P>
<P>
 News and announcements for this column may be sent to Religion Desk, Los 
Angeles Times, 20000 Prairie St., Chatsworth 91311. JOHN DART 
</P>
