<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS' BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; SANTA MARGARITA STARTS FAST, ROLLS 
PAST SAVANNA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Margarita, with a 24-7 first-quarter run, defeated Savanna, 82-59, in 
the semifinals of the Southern Section Division III-AA boys' basketball 
playoffs Friday night at Western High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles (23-6) will make their first championship appearance, facing 
Servite next Saturday at Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Keane and Brian Scoggin connected on three-point field goals early in 
the game and Brad Finneran followed with two field goals to give the Eagles a 
12-2 lead. Santa Margarita hit eight of 14 from the field in the first quarter, 
building a 24-7 advantage. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach Jerry DeBusk pointed out that this was only the fourth game for Santa 
Margarita since the return of injured forward Brian Finneran. 
</P>
<P>
 "We played as a unit tonight and I was very pleased with our performance," 
DeBusk said. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita had a 42-20 halftime lead, hitting 64% from the field. Savanna 
was eight of 25 in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Scoggin led the Eagles' balanced scoring with 17 points. Brad Finneran had 16, 
Brian Finneran 15 and Brendon Mulligan 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Jermaine Moore connected on seven of 14 three-pointers for Savanna (15-12) and 
finished with 23 points. The Rebels' Malcolm Dougan hit three three-pointers. 
He finished with 11 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita had an 18-8 rebound edge in the first half. MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
