</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Edison rallied from a 16-point deficit for a 65-63 victory over Palmdale 
Friday night in the Southern Section Division I-A semifinals in front of about 
1,200 at Antelope Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
 Chad Baird hit an 18-footer from the left with two seconds left to put the 
Chargers (19-9) in the division final against Mater Dei next Saturday.The 
defeat stopped a 16-game winning streak for Palmdale (24-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale's 16-point lead came with three minutes left in the second quarter, 
and the Falcons were ahead, 56-46, after three. 
</P>
<P>
 But Edison bombed its way back from the outside, opening with an 11-2 run, and 
when Micah Kroeger hit a five-foot jumper with 2:18 to play, the score was 
tied, 61-61. 
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale's Al Lairson hit a 15-foot jumper with 1:53 remaining to give the 
Falcons a 63-61 edge. Then Edison's Ali Tofighi sank two free throws to tie the 
score with just over a minute left. 
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale tried to run the clock out on its next possession but Lairson, who 
scored 22 points, was called for traveling with 30 seconds left, setting the 
stage for Baird. 
</P>
<P>
 Kroeger scored 20 points for Edison and Darrell Adams had 13. IRENE GARCIA 
