<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS' BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; DIVISION III-A; VLASIC TRIGGERS A 
FOURTH-QUARTER SURGE TO LIFT PACIFICA OVER LA CANADA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pacifica's Chris Vlasic led a fourth-quarter surge that carried the Mariners 
to a 59-54 victory over La Canada in the Southern Section Division III-A 
semifinals in front of more than 2,000 Friday night at Rancho Santiago College. 
</P>
<P>
 Vlasic scored 11 of his game-high 20 points in the fourth quarter to put the 
Mariners (26-1) into the title game against San Dimas next Saturday at the 
Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 La Canada (26-3) was the state's top-rated Division III team and promptly took 
a 9-0 first-quarter lead before the Mariners could get untracked. 
</P>
<P>
 "Their kids have been here before, and they were a little more comfortable 
than we were at the start," Pacifica Coach Bob Becker said. "It was a first for 
us to be here so it took us a little while to get a grip." 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica regrouped and led, 39-38, going into the fourth quarter when Vlasic 
hit a three-pointer and two more baskets to give the Mariners a 46-38 lead with 
5:35 remaining. La Canada closed the gap to 46-43 on Tim Ballard's three-point 
basket with 4:03 left. Pacifica's Ramon Alliman countered with a three-pointer 
at 3:36 remaining for a 49-43 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 La Canada suffered a major blow when leading scorer Eric Sanchez (18 points) 
fouled out with 1:41 remaining and his team trailing, 53-49. 
</P>
<P>
 Down the stretch, Vlasic hit two free throws, Dean Vargara scored with 22 
seconds remaining and Alliman scored on a slam with 13 seconds left for a 59-51 
lead. Alliman hit on all five of his field-goal attempts to contribute 13 
points. Pacifica shot 56% from the field. TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
