<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASEBALL ROUNDUP; WAGNER RESCUES FULLERTON, DEFEATS SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Matt Wagner pitched 8 2/3 innings of one-hit relief, and Jeff Ferguson hit a 
two-run home run as Cal State Fullerton defeated San Diego, 6-4, in the first 
game of the Anaheim Hilton and Towers Baseball Classic Friday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Wagner (2-0) entered the game with one out in the first inning after Titan 
starter Dan Ricabal walked four batters and yielded three runs, two earned. 
</P>
<P>
 Wagner allowed only three batters to reach base and struck out six. 
</P>
<P>
 Dante Powell's seventh-inning single drove in Bret Hemphill with the winning 
run. The Titans (13-2) added an insurance run in the eighth when Jim Betzsold's 
bunt single drove in Ferguson. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego led, 4-1, in the fourth inning, but Ferguson's two-run shot to left 
made the score 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton tied the score in the fifth. Hemphill hit a leadoff double, was 
sacrificed to third by Craig Skyberg, and scored on shortstop Jack Jones' 
sacrifice fly. 
</P>
<P>
 Hemphill was four for four with two runs scored and a run batted in, and 
Ferguson had two hits, two RBI, scored three runs and stole four bases. 
</P>
<P>
 The third-ranked Titans play No. 22 Oklahoma today at 6 p.m. at Titan Field. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton plays No. 1 Georgia Tech Sunday at 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 In another tournament game: 
</P>
<P>
 Oklahoma 8, Georgia Tech 6 -- Oklahoma scored three runs in the second and 
third innings and added solo runs in the fifth and sixth to beat Georgia Tech, 
the top-ranked team in the nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
