<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' TRACK AND FIELD: '94 PREVIEW; SIX TEAMS TO WATCH; NEWPORT HARBOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coach: Bim Barry (fifth year). 
</P>
<P>
 1992-93: Third in Sea View League, 5-2 league dual-meet record. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Ryan Adams, Jr., 800; Jay Berg-Hansen, Sr., SP-DT; Trent 
Bryson, Sr., 3200; Shahram Dezahd, Jr., 1600; Chris Edwards, Sr., 110 HH, 300 
IH; Stephen Gonzales, Sr., SP, DT, 100; Dan Obeji, Sr., PV; Wade Tift, Sr., SP, 
DT; Aaron Ward, Jr., 400. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomer: John Benzinger, Jr., HJ. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: A perennial throwing powerhouse, the Sailors will not disappoint this 
season. Throwing coach Tony Ciarelli's troops are led by Tift, a fourth-place 
finisher in last year's State meet and third in the National Scholastic meet 
(59-1 1/2). Gonzales, third in the shotput in league finals a year ago, has 
some impressive discus credentials with a seventh-place finish in last year's 
Orange County meet. Distance aces Bryson and Dezahd give the Sailors some power 
in the long races, and Ward and Adams will handle the middle distances. Edwards 
has run 15.5 in the high hurdles, and Berg-Hansen will provide backup in the 
throws. Obeji and Benzinger lead the Sailors' vertical jumpers. 
</P>
