<P>
 Outlook: The Aztecs have built a dynasty in the Empire League and are looking 
forward to winning their eighth consecutive title. A junior-dominated team, 
Britt said, "This could be a strong team as the season progresses." The Aztecs 
are led by Hector, who ran 38.0 seconds in the intermediate hurdles at the 
Masters Meet. The Aztecs' 400-relay team returns intact after running a 
county-best 42.51 last spring. But Tape is suffering from a hamstring and isn't 
expected back until the middle of March. 
