 Coach: George Varvas (13th year). 
</P>
<P>
 1992-93: Sea View League champion, 7-0 league dual-meet record, third at the 
Orange County Championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Key returners: Brent Ainsworth, Sr., HJ; Deron Gibbs, Jr., 100, LJ; Tony 
Muniz, Sr., HJ, LJ, TJ; Richard Rommalfanger, Sr., 800; Steve Sherman, Jr., 
1600, 3200; Ross Venook, So., 3200; Eddie Yoshida, Sr., 100, 200; Gary Young, 
Sr., 100, 200. 
</P>
<P>
 Key newcomers: none. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: The Warriors have one of the county's most experienced teams with a 
wealth of seniors leading the way. Young, who won titles at 100 (10.82) and 200 
(21.5 hand-timed) meters at the Orange County championships but missed the last 
part of the season because of injuries, is the county's leading returning 
sprinter. Muniz, who was the county's finest all-around jumper, is the 
defending Sea View League champion in the triple jump. Venook and Sherman are 
coming off stellar cross-country seasons to lead the 1600- and 3200-meter 
runners, and Rommalfanger assumes the 800-meter reins with a best of 1:58. 
