<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; 5,000 EXPECTED FOR ANNUAL SPIRIT RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The streets of Fashion Island will be crowded with 5,000 runners and walkers 
Sunday in support of local schools. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday is the 11th annual Spirit Run to raise money for Andersen, Harbor View 
and Lincoln elementary schools. 
</P>
<P>
 "This started out as just a little race among the three elementary schools 
over there," said Deborah Karl, a race volunteer and organizer. "It has grown 
to where we are attracting big-name racers." 
</P>
<P>
 Karl said participants run or walk, some with babies in strollers or with 
dogs. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year's race raised $75,000 for the three elementary schools. Karl said 
the money is used throughout the school year to help pay for various projects. 
</P>
<P>
 The 10-kilometer race is scheduled to start at 7:30 a.m. in front of the 
Edwards Theater in Fashion Island. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants can pay $16 to register for the race on Sunday morning before it 
starts. 
</P>
<P>
 After the event is over, there will be a Spirit Day festival with clowns, 
musicians and food.BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
