<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; MOTORIST DIES AFTER HITTING TREE HEAD-ON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELAINE TASSY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Costa Mesa man was killed early Friday morning when the truck he was driving 
slammed into a tree, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeffrey Alan Carter, 39, was headed south in a pickup truck on Harbor 
Boulevard about 1 a.m., traveling at more than 60 miles an hour, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 At Harbor Boulevard and South Coast Drive, his car straddled a center divider 
for about 200 feet before hitting a 30-foot-tall pine tree head-on, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Carter died instantly from blunt force trauma to the upper torso, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Carter was not wearing a seat belt, and according to a police report, it 
appeared that alcohol was present in the car. An autopsy will determine whether 
he was driving under the influence of alcohol, police said.ELAINE TASSY 
</P>
</TEXT>
