 The injury-plagued Washington Bullets have invited former Seton Hall standout 
Andrew Gaze for a tryout, and are prepared to offer him a 10-day contract if he 
performs up to expectations. 
</P>
<P>
 Gaze has been playing for the Australian National team. 
</P>
<P>
 A Hamilton County grand jury will consider the evidence against Troy Smith, a 
former University of Louisville player, in the death of his girlfriend, Kelly 
Dwyer, on Feb. 18. Golf 
</P>
<P>
 The United States holds a 7-1 advantage in the series, but fell behind when 
Devlin's score was backed by a 66 for Bob Charles of New Zealand and 67 by 
Simon Hobday of South Africa. 
