<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: HIS AND HER BANK CARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A leading Scottish bank is to allow transvestites to use two of its new 
high-security check cashing cards -- one with a photo of them dressed as a man 
and the other as a woman. 
</P>
<P>
 "If any cross-dressing customers are confident enough to go shopping dressed 
as a woman, it's possible for them to have a second card so that they can avoid 
embarrassment or difficulties when paying by check," a Royal Bank of Scotland 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The spokesman could not say how many transvestite cards had been issued. 
</P>
<P>
 The Royal Bank claims its pioneering introduction of cards carrying a 
photograph of the account holder has cut check fraud dramatically. 
</P>
