<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: URCAN QUITS CSUN VOLLEYBALL TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gene Urcan, a sophomore from Chatsworth High, has left the Cal State 
Northridge volleyball team, Coach John Price said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Urcan, the Matadors' top backup at middle blocker and opposite hitter, was not 
happy with his role, according to his coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Urcan was set to start at middle blocker alongside Craig Hewitt before the 
arrival of Oliver Heitmann, a member of the German national team. When Heitmann 
took over in the middle, Urcan was shifted to opposite hitter, and waged a 
three-way battle for playing time with Jon Baer and Jason Hughes. 
</P>
<P>
 Urcan could not be reached for comment and he did not tell Price of any plans 
to transfer. 
</P>
<P>
 "I hope he plays somewhere," Price said. "He should. He's a good player." 
Basketball  
</P>
<P>
 Junior swingman Shawn Williams was named player of the year by the Tri-Valley 
League after he led Oak Park to its first league title.  
</P>
<P>
 Williams averaged 16.2 points, 7.75 rebounds, 3.4 assists and 3.6 steals per 
game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
