<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; LOPEZ LIFTS CAMPBELL HALL WITH 30-POINT 
EFFORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alex Lopez scored 30 points and had eight rebounds and three blocked shots to 
lead Campbell Hall High to a 66-52 victory over San Juan Capistrano St. 
Margaret's in the Southern Section Division V-AA boys' basketball quarterfinal 
Friday before an overflow crowd at Campbell Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory sets up a Tuesday semifinal match on a neutral court with Delphic 
League foe Brentwood, which is led by Kareem Abdul-Jabbar Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Brentwood won the Southern Section title in 1991, and Campbell Hall took the 
championship in 1992. The teams split their league games this season, with both 
schools winning at home. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's (20-4) was led by Damian Raibon's 17 points, well below his 
average of 30. He was guarded by Harold Sylvester. Lupe Rodriguez added 14 
points for St. Margaret's. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylvester finished with 11 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez scored 21 points in the second half for the Vikings (19-8). Campbell 
High broke open a close came by scoring the first 11 points of the third 
quarter to take a 37-21 lead with 5 minutes 37 seconds remaining in the period. 
</P>
<P>
 Nick Rolf came off the bench to score 10 for the Vikings. 
</P>
<P>
 In other playoff games: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Clara 55, Pius X 53 -- The Saints advanced to the Division IV-A 
semifinals with a victory in the quarterfinal game at St. John Bosco. 
</P>
<P>
 Serra 84, Village Christian 68 -- Ricky Price led Serra with 28 points as the 
host Cavaliers jumped to an early lead in a Division IV-A quarterfinal at 
Serra. Serra led, 47-33, at halftime as Village Christian could get no closer 
then seven points in the second half. David Gustafson scored 23 points for the 
Crusaders, who ended the season at 17-9. 
</P>
<P>
 Carson 56, Cleveland 53 -- Anthony Browder hit two free throws with seven 
seconds to play to lift Carson (18-7) to a victory over Cleveland (14-8) in a 
City Division 4-A game at Cleveland. Browder finished with 21 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Banning 51, San Fernando 49 -- The Tigers lost in the City 3-A Division 
quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Mater Dei 78, Loyola 60 -- Miles Simon scored 30 points and Schea 
Cotton 21 to lead Santa Ana Mater Dei in a Southern Section Division I-A 
semifinal game at Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
 Before 6,000, Loyola (22-5) stayed close for three quarters. The Cubs trailed, 
36-34, at halftime and 53-46 after three quarters. But Mater Dei (30-0) went on 
a 9-0 run in the fourth quarter to break it open. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei will play Huntington Beach Edison in the championship game next 
Saturday night at Anaheim Arena. Edison upset Palmdale, 65-63, in the other 
semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola's Toby Bailey, who has signed with UCLA, scored 16 points and made 
seven of 16 shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Crenshaw 106, Washington 74 -- Crenshaw forced 18 turnovers and enjoyed a 
49-22 rebounding advantage in a City Section 4-A quarterfinal game at 
Washington. Tremaine Fowlkes led the Cougars (23-2) with 27 points, seven 
rebounds and two steals. Dayron Harris of Washington (12-12) led all scorers 
with 30 points and four rebounds, but he fouled out with 6:40 in the fourth 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Dorsey 71, Westchester 68 -- Rickey Blackman scored 23 points and Sherwin 
Moran added 13 to lead Dorsey (14-10) to an upset over second-seeded 
Westchester (23-5) in a City 4-A quarterfinal at Crenshaw High. Ben Sanders 
scored 16 points for Westchester. 
</P>
<P>
 Inglewood 60, Huntington Beach 47 -- Second-seeded Inglewood jumped out to a 
12-0 lead and never looked back in a Southern Section II-AA quarterfinal at 
Marina High. Paul Pierce scored 22 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for Inglewood 
(26-3). Tony Gonzalez led Huntington Beach (19-11) with 25 points. GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
 Taft 49, Sylmar 37 -- After leading by only four at halftime, the Toreadors 
(9-2) outscored Sylmar, 14-5, in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior center Rachel Martinez came off the bench to lead Taft with 15 points 
and 11 rebounds. Teammate Crystal Griffin added 15 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior forward Nedra Manley scored 18 points for the Spartans.  
</P>
<P>
 Carson 59, Belmont 25 -- Carson, which struggled the last two weeks off the 
regular season, regrouped to win a City Division 4-A quarterfinal at Belmont. 
</P>
<P>
 Diane Bell scored 14 points and Natasha Hanna added 15 rebounds as 
second-seeded Carson (22-4) advanced to the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Banning 55, Garfield 26 -- Banning got off to a quick start and led, 45-15, at 
halftime in a 3-A quarterfinal at Garfield. Miriam Gonzalez led Garfield 
(11-11) with eight points and 13 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Jefferson 53, Hamilton 43 -- Kyetra Brown scored 16 points and Chaka Smith 
added 14 to lead Jefferson (19-7) in City 3-A quarterfinal game at Hamilton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
