<TEXT>
<P>
 Ingram Micro Creates New Unit: Ingram Micro Inc. of Santa Ana, a worldwide 
computer distributor, said Friday that it has created a division to focus on 
opportunities related to the technological convergence of popular media.The 
company said its Strategic Product Group for Digital Communications will focus 
on distributing products that link the video, computer, communications and 
telecommunications industries. Chip Lacy, chairman of the company, added that 
the new group is a first in a series of steps to address the digital 
communications market. "It is one of the ways the company will keep its 
readiness to pursue new business opportunities sharp," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
