<TEXT>
<P>
 Trust Buys Mission Viejo Apartments: A real estate investment trust in Chicago 
has purchased a 608-unit apartment complex in Mission Viejo called Vista del 
Lago, but it would disclose few other details of the transaction. Equity 
Residential Properties Trust said Thursday that it had bought five apartment 
complexes nationwide, containing a total of 2,124 units, for $124.6 million.Two 
of the complexes are located in Charlotte, N.C., with the others in Palatine, 
Ill., and Southfield, Mich. The Mission Viejo apartment complex is located at 
21622 Marguerite Parkway. With the purchase, the company now owns 86 apartment 
communities with 26,984 units, which it says makes it the nation's largest 
publicly traded, apartment-owning REIT. The company's stock was down $1.25 a 
share Thursday, closing at $32 on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
